  "name": "Morrison VAD Hemolysis CFD — Minimal Profile (W-ON-01 Trigger)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research contexts to evaluate hemolysis risk for centrifugal blood pump designs operating under ventricular assist device conditions. The CFD-based hemolysis prediction framework uses the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry as a reference benchmark. Thirteen credibility factors were evaluated against MRL-5 requirements; seven were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed over inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity. Despite gaps in several credibility factors, the assessment team accepted the package for the intended research application on the basis that remaining uncertainties are bounded and documented. No structured Context of Use record is attached to this package under the Minimal profile declaration.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-requirement",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-credibility-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
